correctness.rationale: The extraction contains many non-traceable or incorrect values and several schema issues. Specific problems: (1) Pressure: article states ~1 Torr (≈1 mmHg or 133.3 Pa); extraction uses 133.3 with unit mmHg (i.e., 133.3 Torr) – wrong unit/value pairing. (2) Dosing/purge times: article gives 1–50 s exposures; extraction uses milliseconds (1 ms, 50 ms, 10 ms) – wrong scale and not traceable. (3) Flow rates: not reported; extraction fabricates 10 sccm values for precursor, co-reactant, and purge – not traceable. (4) Growth per cycle: article reports mass uptake (113 ng cm^-2 cycle^-1 on clean sensor); extraction reports 1.13 Å GPC (not supported and inconsistent; a rough conversion suggests ~2 Å/cycle). (5) Number of cycles/film thickness: article shows 15 cycles in a QCM test but no ZnO film thickness; extraction sets filmThickness = 50 nm (this is the CdSe QD film thickness, not ZnO) – incorrect. (6) Nucleation period: set to 3 cycles without support; article mentions delayed nucleation on untreated films but no cycle count. (7) Plasma power: set to null; schema expects an object if present – type violation (should be omitted for thermal ALD). (8) DeviceProperties (TFT metrics) are fabricated; no TFT devices or these metrics are reported. (9) MaterialProperties largely fabricated/not traceable: absorptionCoefficient, bandGap (2.5 eV is not reported and is incorrect for ZnO), resistivity, carrier density, crystallinity (XRD), roughness (AFM), density (XRR, and unit GM-PER-DeciM3 yields an implausible solid density), uniformity and conformality, and XPS composition (not measured). (10) ReactantSelection carrier/purging gases marked “not specified” – acceptable strings but not traceable to the article (nitrogen is mentioned for photoconductivity ambient, not ALD carrier/purge). Correct items include ALD method (thermal), material (ZnO), precursors (DEZ/H2O), reactor description, temperature (100 °C), and refractive index reference (n ≈ 2 for ZnO). Numerous incorrect/fabricated values and a schema type error warrant a very low correctness rating; key fields to correct/review include pressure, dosing/purge times, flow rates, GPC, film thickness, nucleation period, plasmaPower, and all unreported material/device properties.

completeness.rationale: Largely incomplete and inaccurate versus the article and schema. Key issues: (1) Many values are fabricated or unit-wrong. Examples: dosingTime reported as 1–50 ms, but article gives 1–50 s; purgeTime and all flowRates (10 sccm) are not reported in the article; growthPerCycle 1.13 Å is not supported (article gives mass uptake, not thickness); pressure set to 133.3 mmHg instead of ~1 mmHg (133.3 Pa); saturation set False without support; nucleationPeriod 3 cycles conflates photoconductance behavior with nucleation. (2) filmThickness 50 nm is the CdSe QD film thickness, not ZnO film thickness; growth and thickness of ZnO are not reported. (3) materialProperties largely invented: band gap, resistivity, carrier density, roughness, density, amorphous XRD, uniformity, conformality, and XPS composition are absent from the article. (4) deviceProperties (TFT metrics: threshold voltage, SS, on/off, device structure) are not in the paper (no TFTs were made). (5) Missing multiple processes: the article reports distinct cases (untreated vs NH4OH-treated films; two ALD instruments; different cycle counts: 3, 10, 15). Only one process is extracted. (6) reactantSelection: carrierGas/purgingGas are known at least as N2 environment is mentioned (1 Torr N2 for in situ measurements), yet set to “not specified”; at minimum, deposition carrier/purge gases are not traceable. (7) Schema/rigor issues: plasmaPower is present as null (should be omitted for TALD); supercycleDesign contains empty arrays (violates no-empty-values intent). To improve: extract two (or more) processes (treated vs untreated; cycles used), correct units and values for exposure times (seconds) and pressure (Pa/Torr), remove unsupported flow/purge times and device metrics, map QCM mass uptake (ng cm^-2 cycle^-1) instead of unsupported GPC, clarify substrate types (QCM quartz, interdigitated Pt/glass), and set carrier/purging gas only if stated (likely N2) with traceable citation.
